Wallet Compromise Checker 

A security-focused GitHub application that scans blockchain wallet activity for signs of compromise, malicious approvals, phishing exposure, wallet drainers, suspicious transactions, leaked private keys, and risky smart contract interactions.

The Wallet Compromise Checker helps users and developers quickly assess the safety status of crypto wallets across multiple chains by analyzing on-chain behavior, token approvals, transaction patterns, blacklist databases, and known exploit signatures.

Features

Multi-chain wallet security analysis

Detect malicious token approvals

Wallet drainer & phishing detection

Smart contract risk assessment

Transaction anomaly monitoring

Compromised wallet reputation scoring

Real-time threat intelligence integration

Private key leak monitoring

Suspicious NFT & token interaction alerts

API support for developers and security tools


Use Cases

Check if a wallet has been compromised

Audit wallet permissions before trading

Monitor DAO treasury wallets

Protect users from phishing attacks

Integrate wallet security checks into dApps

Risk scoring for Web3 onboarding systems


Tech Stack

Built with modern Web3 tooling including blockchain RPC providers, threat intelligence APIs, smart contract analyzers, and secure backend infrastructure.

